      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think there\u0027s a pattern that we can offer to let constructors stay private and friendless:\n\n#include \u003cnew\u003e\n#include \u003ctype_traits\u003e\n\nclass Alloc {\npublic:\n    template \u003ctypename Constructor\u003e\n    auto make(Constructor\u0026\u0026 ctor) {\n        using T \u003d std::remove_pointer_t\u003cdecltype(ctor(nullptr))\u003e;\n\n        void* ptr \u003d this-\u003ealloc(sizeof(T), alignof(T));\n        return ctor(ptr);\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    void* alloc(size_t size, size_t align);\n};\n\nclass Foo {\npublic:\n    Foo* make(Alloc* alloc, float f) {\n        return alloc-\u003emake([\u0026](void* ptr) {\n            return new (ptr) Foo(f);\n        });\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    Foo(float);\n};",
